article.headline: UC Santa Barbara 67, Sonoma State 66
article.story: SANTA BARBARA, Calif. (AP) -- Cecil Brown made a pair of 3-pointers in the final 50 seconds including the game-winner at the buzzer to rally UC Santa Barbara to a 67-66 victory over Sonoma State. The Gauchos (4-4) were led by Cameron Goettsche, who scored 18 of his 21 points in the second half. He also had seven rebounds and two blocked shots. Sonoma State (4-4) got 17 points from Vince Inglima, including eight in the final five minutes. His layup put the Seawolves up 66-64 with 7.8 seconds left. UC Santa Barbara set up for a final play under its own basket with 1.8 seconds to go. Alex Harris inbounded the ball to Brown in the right corner for his decisive 3-pointer. Brown finished with 18 points. Chris Devine added 14, including six in the final four minutes to help UC Santa Barbara rally from a 60-55 deficit. J.T. Tipton had 13 points and seven rebounds for the Seawolves, who outshot the Gauchos 52.2 to 46 percent.
